defs.name: Document
defs.docs: An HTML document.

defs.name: find
defs.docs: Returns a `Selection` containing nodes passing the given predicate `p`.

defs.name: nth
defs.docs:
Returns the `n`th node of the document as a `Some(Node)`, indexed from
 0, or `None` if n is greater than or equal to the number of nodes.

defs.name: Data
defs.docs: The Node type specific data stored by every Node.

defs.name: Raw
defs.value: Raw { index, parent, prev, next, first_child, last_child, data }
defs.docs:
Internal representation of a Node. Not of much use without a reference to a
 Document.

defs.name: Node
defs.docs: A single node of an HTML document. Nodes may be HTML elements, comments, or text nodes.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a Node referring to the `index`th Node of a document.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: Get the index of this Node in its Document.

defs.name: raw
defs.docs: Obtain the inner representation of this Node.

defs.name: data
defs.docs: Get the text node, HTML element, or comment from a Node.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Get the name of a Node if it is an HTML element, or None otherwise.

defs.name: attr
defs.docs: Get the value of the attribute `name` from a Node representing a HTML element.

defs.name: attrs
defs.docs:
Get an iterator over the names and values of attributes of the Element.
 Returns an empty iterator for non Element nodes.

defs.name: text
defs.docs: Get the combined textual content of a Node and all of its children.

defs.name: html
defs.docs: Serialize a Node to an HTML string.

defs.name: inner_html
defs.docs: Serialize a Node's children to an HTML string.

defs.name: find
defs.docs: Search for Nodes fulfilling `predicate` in the descendants of a Node.

defs.name: is
defs.docs: Evaluate a predicate on this Node.

defs.name: as_text
defs.docs: Get the text of a text Node, or None if the node is not text.

defs.name: as_comment
defs.docs: Get the text of a comment Node, or None if the node is not a comment.

defs.name: children
defs.docs: Construct an iterator over a Node's child Nodes.

defs.name: descendants
defs.docs: Construct an iterator over a Node's descendant (transitive children) Nodes.

defs.name: Predicate
defs.docs: A trait implemented by all `Node` matchers.

defs.name: Any
defs.docs: Matches any Node.

defs.name: Name
defs.docs: Matches Element Node with name `T`.

defs.name: Class
defs.docs: Matches Element Node containing class `T`.

defs.name: Not
defs.docs: Matches if the Predicate `T` does not match.

defs.name: Attr
defs.docs:
Matches Element Node containing attribute `N` with value `V` if `V` is an
 `&str`, or any value if `V` is `()`.

defs.name: Element
defs.docs: Matches any Element Node.

defs.name: Text
defs.docs: Matches any Text Node.

defs.name: Comment
defs.docs: Matches any Comment Node.

defs.name: Or
defs.docs: Matches if either inner Predicate `A` or `B` matches the Node.

defs.name: And
defs.docs: Matches if the inner Predicate `A` and `B` both match the Node.

defs.name: Child
defs.docs:
Matches if inner Predicate `B` matches the node and `A` matches the parent
 of the node.

defs.name: Descendant
defs.docs:
Matches if inner Predicate `B` matches the node and `A` matches any of the
 parents of node.
